---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About — Labi Joshua"
  description="I'm a product designer who loves figuring out how things work and how they are made."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="pt-16 pb-12 px-6 text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto">
    <span class="inline-block border border-dashed border-neutral-300 bg-neutral-100 rounded-full px-4 py-1 text-xs tracking-wide mb-6" style="color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);">
      This is me
    </span>
    <h1 class="font-serif text-5xl md:text-[52px] leading-[1.15] tracking-tight text-neutral-900">
      Welcome to my corner of the Interweb.
    </h1>
  </section>

  <div class="max-w-[1100px] mx-auto px-6">

    <!-- Intro: Photo + Bio -->
    <section class="grid md:grid-cols-[5fr_7fr] gap-12 mb-16">
      <div class="rounded-3xl overflow-hidden bg-neutral-200" style="aspect-ratio: 3/4;">
        <img
          src="/images/about-profile.jpg"
          alt="Labi Joshua standing in an art gallery"
          class="w-full h-full object-cover object-center"
          loading="eager"
        />
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-col justify-center gap-5 pl-2">
        <h2 class="font-serif leading-tight text-neutral-900" style="font-size: 40px;">
          <span style="color: #51782B;">Hi!</span> I'm Labi Joshua.
        </h2>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-3 text-sm text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
          <p>I am a product designer who loves figuring out how things work and how they are made.</p>
          <p>My journey started when I studied Industrial Design at FUTA. There, I learned to build and shape physical objects. In my second year, I discovered digital product design and started playing with how things look and now people use them. I realized that whether I am making a physical tool or a digital app, the same rule applies. The craft matters.</p>
          <p>Now, I spend most of my time focusing on the work behind the scenes. I am interested in finding better ways to get things done. I build systems and tools that make my work smooth and easy. My goal is to build systems that help me be more creative.</p>
          <p>Outside of work, you can find me watching a funny sitcom or looking at art. I am not a painter, but I have a lot of respect for the hard work and ideas that go into making art. I bring that same respect to my design work. I am always looking for ways to combine solid structure with creative ideas.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Stats -->
    <section class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden mb-16" style="background-color: #F5F5F5;">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 divide-y md:divide-y-0 md:divide-x divide-neutral-200">
        <div class="px-6 py-6 flex flex-col gap-1.5">
          <span class="text-xs text-neutral-400">Based in:</span>
          <span class="font-serif text-2xl" style="color: #51782B;">Lagos, Nigeria</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-neutral-400 mt-4">UTC+1, Always available.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="px-6 py-6 flex flex-col gap-1.5">
          <span class="text-xs text-neutral-400">Doing this for:</span>
          <span class="font-serif text-2xl" style="color: #51782B;">3+ years</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-neutral-400 mt-4">A lifetime of making things with my hands.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="px-6 py-6 flex flex-col gap-1.5">
          <span class="text-xs text-neutral-400">Off the clock:</span>
          <span class="font-serif text-2xl" style="color: #51782B;">Creative Consumer</span>
          <span class="text-xs text-neutral-400 mt-4">Obsessed with sitcoms and art history.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Gallery -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-5">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-neutral-600">
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
            <line x1="2" y1="12" x2="22" y2="12"/>
            <path d="M12 2a15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4 10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1-4-10 15.3 15.3 0 0 1 4-10z"/>
          </svg>
          Welcome to my world
        </div>
        <span class="text-sm text-neutral-400">Gallery</span>
      </div>

      <!-- Desktop grid (3-col asymmetric) -->
      <div class="hidden md:grid gap-3" style="grid-template-columns: 2fr 1.3fr 1fr; grid-template-rows: 1fr 1fr; height: 420px;">
        <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-neutral-200" style="grid-row: 1 / 3;">
          <img src="/images/gallery-desk.jpg" alt="Labi Joshua at his workspace" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-neutral-300" style="grid-row: 1 / 3;">
          <img src="/images/gallery-cap.jpg" alt="Labi Joshua" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-neutral-200">
          <img src="/images/gallery-street.jpg" alt="" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-neutral-300">
          <img src="/images/gallery-friends.jpg" alt="" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Mobile grid (2-col: large left, 2 stacked right) -->
      <div class="md:hidden grid grid-cols-2 gap-3" style="height: 300px;">
        <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-neutral-200 row-span-2">
          <img src="/images/gallery-desk.jpg" alt="Labi Joshua at his workspace" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-neutral-300">
          <img src="/images/gallery-cap.jpg" alt="Labi Joshua" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-neutral-200">
          <img src="/images/gallery-friends.jpg" alt="" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Me outside of work -->
    <section class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 mb-20 items-start">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-[40px] md:text-[44px] leading-tight text-neutral-900">
        Me outside of work
      </h2>
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          I keep my downtime creative. You will likely find me getting inspired by shows like Abstract, or tuning into Sticky Notes and The Futur to keep my design mind sharp.
        </p>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-blue-700" style="aspect-ratio: 16/10;">
            <img src="/images/thefutur.jpg" alt="The Futur" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-red-500" style="aspect-ratio: 16/10;">
            <img src="/images/stickynotes.jpg" alt="Sticky Notes" class="w-full h-full object-cover" loading="lazy" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- How I work -->
    <section class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 mb-20 items-start">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-[40px] md:text-[44px] leading-tight text-neutral-900">
        How I work
      </h2>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed">
        I start by finding the real problem so I can build the best solution. I focus on making systems that are simple and built to last. I always try to improve my work and tools to make things run smoothly. Finally, I stay curious by looking at art and stories to find new ideas for my projects.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Say hi -->
    <section class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-10 mb-20 items-start">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-[40px] md:text-[44px] leading-tight text-neutral-900">
        Say hi.
      </h2>
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 leading-relaxed mb-6">
          I'm currently taking on one new project for Q3 2026 — and always happy to swap notes on systems, tokens, or what to lift on a Tuesday. The fastest way is email.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
          <a
            href="mailto:jospecial34@gmail.com"
            class="flex flex-col gap-1 border border-dashed border-neutral-300 rounded-2xl px-5 py-3 hover:border-neutral-400 transition-colors"
          >
            <span class="text-xs text-neutral-400">Email</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-neutral-700 font-medium">jospecial34@gmail.com</span>
          </a>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-1 border border-dashed border-neutral-300 rounded-2xl px-5 py-3">
            <span class="text-xs text-neutral-400">Phone number</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-neutral-700 font-medium">+234 816 9203 595</span>
          </div>
          <a
            href="https://twitter.com/Labi_Joshua"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="flex flex-col gap-1 border border-dashed border-neutral-300 rounded-2xl px-5 py-3 hover:border-neutral-400 transition-colors"
          >
            <span class="text-xs text-neutral-400">Twitter</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-neutral-700 font-medium">@Labi_Joshua</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

</Layout>
